# branding.exclude — repo-relative paths the JARVIS overlay must NEVER brand
# or revert. Use this for files you maintain your own local patches to: the
# overlay leaves them completely alone, so `update-jarvis.sh` never reverts
# your changes and never re-brands them.
#
# One path per line, relative to the Hermes source root. '#' starts a comment.
# (You can also pass paths at runtime via the JARVIS_EXCLUDE env var.)
#
# Example — an operator who has hand-patched the QQ adapter and gateway:
# gateway/platforms/qqbot/adapter.py
# gateway/run.py
